column10: Learning and Skills Council (LSC) - East Midlands
column11: Details from DWP: The project funding totals in column 3 of the first seven and a half pages are all based on 100% ESF funding. The last one and a half pages of the list relate to ‘Response to Redundancy’ projects which are 50% ESF and 50% Skills Funding Agency match funded.  All current regional Skills Funding Agency (formerly Learning and Skill Council) project lists on the website include 100% ESF funded projects and most include some 50% ESF and 50% public match ‘Response to Redundancy’ projects. The Skills Funding Agency also identifies match funding directly related to individual participants from a range of government funded employment and skills provision.

column11: Details from DWP: Priority 1 list: Priority 1 list: The first six projects are contracted by Lincolnshire County Council. These are funded at 45% ESF and 55% public match funding. Derbyshire County Council’s Mencap project contract is funded at 100% ESF. This is matched against the next contract on the list - McIntyre which is 100% match funding. Apex & Employment Opportunities ESF projects are contracted by Leicester City Council. These are funded at 45% ESF and 55% public match funding. Jobs, Education & Training - Raising Aspirations (JET) is a Derby City Partnership ESF funded project. Funding is 50% ESF and 50% public match funding. Priority 2 list: NBV Ltd, Lincolnshire CDA, LCVYS & Urban Challenge are all Lincolnshire are 45% ESF and 55% match from Lincolnshire City Council). Somali Development Services & the Bangladesh Youth & Cultural Shomiti are Leicester City Council ESF funded projects. Funding is 45% ESF & 55% public match funding. Jobs, Education & Training - Avenues for Advancement (JET) is a Derby City Partnership ESF funded project. Funding is 50% ESF and 50% public match.
